9
00:04:04.000 --> 00:04:07.208
yeah. yeah. I get the
pharmacy's texts too.

10
00:04:08.125 --> 00:04:09.166
Right.

11
00:04:12.458 --> 00:04:13.541
Yeah. good.

12
00:04:28.833 --> 00:04:31.767
- Wally. hey!
- Hello. darling.

13
00:04:31.791 --> 00:04:33.976
- Let me help you with that.
- No. I got it.

14
00:04:34.000 --> 00:04:37.892
No need. I'm just… relics I
dug out of the storage space.

15
00:04:37.916 --> 00:04:39.892
Doing an experiment?

16
00:04:39.916 --> 00:04:42.892
No. Sam is helping me put together

17
00:04:42.916 --> 00:04:47.392
a fundamentals of science class
I'm. doing at the community center.

18
00:04:47.416 --> 00:04:49.392
I thought you were banned.

19
00:04:49.416 --> 00:04:51.809
Well. gotta get back in their good graces.

20
00:04:51.833 --> 00:04:55.434
You have been spending a lot of
time with Sam the last few days.

21
00:04:55.458 --> 00:04:59.017
Well. you know I like a fixer-upper. now.

22
00:04:59.041 --> 00:05:00.434
So excuse me.

23
00:05:00.458 --> 00:05:03.916
Science. like myself. waits for no man.

24
00:05:10.625 --> 00:05:14.541
Honey! I'm home!

25
00:05:15.291 --> 00:05:19.726
I just added two dedicated
20-amp circuits to the main panel.

26
00:05:19.750 --> 00:05:21.767
so we shouldn't have any more blowouts.

27
00:05:21.791 --> 00:05:24.434
Wonderful! Now. how
about fixing the fucking lights?

28
00:05:24.458 --> 00:05:25.625
Yeah. It's on the list.

29
00:05:27.625 --> 00:05:28.684
What's this?

30
00:05:28.708 --> 00:05:32.892
The last parts for our brand-new.
slightly used hplc machine.

31
00:05:32.916 --> 00:05:35.291
What exactly does an hplc machine do?

32
00:05:36.166 --> 00:05:37.767
It should finally tell us

33
00:05:37.791 --> 00:05:41.142
what kind of creature your
star-spangled goo came from.

34
00:05:41.166 --> 00:05:42.726
How much did it cost?

35
00:05:42.750 --> 00:05:46.833
Seven… give or take… thousand?

36
00:05:47.416 --> 00:05:48.642
Can't take it with you. Sam.

37
00:05:48.666 --> 00:05:50.546
The pharaohs tried. All
it got them was looted.

38
00:05:52.000 --> 00:05:54.351
- Who the hell is that?
- It's probably Judy.

39
00:05:54.375 --> 00:05:57.458
- Nancy drew knows we're up to something.
- I'll get rid of her.

40
00:05:58.875 --> 00:06:01.083
- Heya!
- Neil.

41
00:06:01.583 --> 00:06:02.601
What are you doing?

42
00:06:02.625 --> 00:06:06.017
Whoa! Looks like a
bomb went off in there.

43
00:06:06.041 --> 00:06:07.184
You're Neil?

44
00:06:07.208 --> 00:06:09.642
- Hey!
- I've heard so much about you.

45
00:06:09.666 --> 00:06:11.000
Doing a little remodeling.

46
00:06:12.166 --> 00:06:14.392
That's a big step. I'm proud of you. pop.

47
00:06:14.416 --> 00:06:18.601
- Yeah. what can I do for you. Neil?
- I need to get Claire's mom's album.

48
00:06:18.625 --> 00:06:19.601
Album?

49
00:06:19.625 --> 00:06:22.726
Yeah. Bruce Springsteen. born to run.

50
00:06:22.750 --> 00:06:25.000
Right. yeah. I'm still looking for it.

51
00:06:25.583 --> 00:06:27.458
- You promised Claire.
- Yeah. I know.

52
00:06:28.208 --> 00:06:30.750
- Haven't found it yet. I've been busy.
- Remodeling.

53
00:06:32.166 --> 00:06:33.684
Appreciate you coming. Neil.

54
00:06:33.708 --> 00:06:36.559
Hey. I've been doing
some reading on loss.

55
00:06:36.583 --> 00:06:40.101
and I found this book that I
think would be really good for you.

56
00:06:40.125 --> 00:06:43.601
It's an exciting new gloss
on Elisabeth kübler-Ross.

57
00:06:43.625 --> 00:06:47.184
And it recontextualizes
the healing process

58
00:06:47.208 --> 00:06:49.392
into a really interesting new concept.

59
00:06:49.416 --> 00:06:52.267
See. kübler-Ross saw
grief as a linear progression

60
00:06:52.291 --> 00:06:57.851
through the stages. right. so it's
denial. anger. sadness. et cetera.

61
00:06:57.875 --> 00:07:01.166
but this posits grief as a pyramid.

62
00:07:01.750 --> 00:07:03.726
- Pyramid?
- With acceptance at the bottom...

63
00:07:03.750 --> 00:07:05.059
you should get going. Neil.

64
00:07:05.083 --> 00:07:07.875
You don't want to get caught
up in all that rush-hour traffic.

65
00:07:10.208 --> 00:07:11.208
Right.

66
00:07:14.833 --> 00:07:15.833
You know.

67
00:07:16.875 --> 00:07:17.875
I get it.

68
00:07:18.375 --> 00:07:20.059
You're not that fond of me.

69
00:07:20.083 --> 00:07:21.083
Okay.

70
00:07:21.833 --> 00:07:23.958
But I came here for Claire.

71
00:07:24.958 --> 00:07:26.000
She's hurting.

72
00:07:27.000 --> 00:07:28.666
Just as much as you are.

73
00:07:29.291 --> 00:07:33.625
So I get that you can't see through
your own pain right now. I get it.

74
00:07:35.458 --> 00:07:39.083
But you're a dad. so you have to.

75
00:07:55.666 --> 00:07:57.101
Hey. It's me.

76
00:07:57.125 --> 00:07:58.392
Hey. it's Erica.

77
00:07:58.416 --> 00:08:00.767
I ran that name you
gave me through ncic.

78
00:08:00.791 --> 00:08:03.434
n-Dex. and a buddy at Chicago pd.

79
00:08:03.458 --> 00:08:04.476
What you got?

80
00:08:04.500 --> 00:08:07.434
A couple of speeding tickets. That's all.

81
00:08:07.458 --> 00:08:09.375
Sam Cooper is a boy scout.

82
00:08:11.458 --> 00:08:12.666
Okay.

83
00:08:13.500 --> 00:08:14.583
All right.

84
00:08:16.291 --> 00:08:18.101
Thanks. Erica.

85
00:08:18.125 --> 00:08:20.517
So. does this mean
you're back on the beat?

86
00:08:20.541 --> 00:08:22.017
You working for a paper?

87
00:08:22.041 --> 00:08:26.041
No. no. god. I'm still retired.

88
00:08:26.666 --> 00:08:28.809
Just trying to help out a friend.

89
00:08:30.833 --> 00:08:32.267
Hey. we gotta catch up.

90
00:08:32.291 --> 00:08:33.476
We should do that.

91
00:08:33.500 --> 00:08:34.476
Okay. Right.

92
00:08:34.500 --> 00:08:35.833
- Bye.
- Bye-bye.

93
00:08:39.583 --> 00:08:41.351
That is bullshit.

94
00:08:41.375 --> 00:08:44.601
You agreed that I
would have the royalties.

95
00:08:44.625 --> 00:08:46.684
It's all I have...

96
00:08:46.708 --> 00:08:49.291
- there you go. Okay.
- Yeah. Thank you.

97
00:08:56.291 --> 00:08:57.517
Hey. kiddo.

98
00:08:57.541 --> 00:08:59.250
Hey. art. Thank you.

99
00:09:01.041 --> 00:09:02.101
You all right?

100
00:09:02.125 --> 00:09:04.517
My ex is suing me.

101
00:09:04.541 --> 00:09:05.934
Again?

102
00:09:05.958 --> 00:09:07.000
Again.

103
00:09:08.000 --> 00:09:10.976
- I'm sorry.
- Yeah.

104
00:09:11.000 --> 00:09:13.476
Better than being married
to him. though. right?

105
00:09:13.500 --> 00:09:15.041
Big time.

106
00:09:18.250 --> 00:09:21.750
"The wise are wise
only because they love."

107
00:09:22.708 --> 00:09:26.916
"Fools are fools only because
they think they can understand love."

108
00:09:28.250 --> 00:09:29.309
Paulo coelho?

109
00:09:29.333 --> 00:09:30.976
Or Wiz Khalifa.

110
00:09:31.000 --> 00:09:32.791
It's not Wiz Khalifa.

111
00:09:33.375 --> 00:09:36.041
- Paulo coelho. it is.
- Okay. All right.

112
00:09:38.708 --> 00:09:39.916
Yeah.

113
00:09:42.666 --> 00:09:43.666
How you doing. art?

114
00:09:44.333 --> 00:09:45.375
Me?

115
00:09:46.375 --> 00:09:47.958
I'm on my quest.

116
00:09:48.916 --> 00:09:50.833
And I better get back to it.

117
00:09:51.791 --> 00:09:54.916
- You keep your chin up. kiddo. All right.
- All right. you too.

118
00:09:59.041 --> 00:10:01.392
- Right-handed chirality!
- Shit!

119
00:10:01.416 --> 00:10:03.726
- Right-handed chirality!
- What? What is...

120
00:10:03.750 --> 00:10:07.142
listen. Every living creature on
earth is made up of amino acids

121
00:10:07.166 --> 00:10:09.184
that have left-handed chirality.

122
00:10:09.208 --> 00:10:11.601
That's how they can
interact. It's like a handshake.

123
00:10:11.625 --> 00:10:14.976
Can't shake hands with left and
right. You'd have to have two left hands.

124
00:10:15.000 --> 00:10:15.892
Same with cells.

125
00:10:15.916 --> 00:10:18.559
But the results from the hplc

126
00:10:18.583 --> 00:10:22.226
show that blood from our
hammer has right-handed chirality.

127
00:10:22.250 --> 00:10:23.517
So what killed Jack?

128
00:10:23.541 --> 00:10:24.851
That's the point.

129
00:10:24.875 --> 00:10:27.726
This is something that
nobody has ever seen before.

130
00:10:27.750 --> 00:10:29.267
Which means you don't have shit?

131
00:10:29.291 --> 00:10:31.976
God. Science isn't magic. Sam!

132
00:10:32.000 --> 00:10:36.267
You spent $7.000. and you
don't know what this thing is!

133
00:10:36.291 --> 00:10:39.559
No. I spent $7.000. and
now I know what it's not.

134
00:10:39.583 --> 00:10:42.392
It is not a. coyote with mange.

135
00:10:42.416 --> 00:10:45.392
It is not a shaved chimpanzee.

136
00:10:45.416 --> 00:10:49.708
It is not a figment of your imagination.

137
00:10:52.666 --> 00:10:56.726
- All right. So what do we do now?
- So now we figure out what it is.

138
00:10:56.750 --> 00:10:57.851
More tests?

139
00:10:57.875 --> 00:10:59.434
Yeah. that might be a problem.

140
00:10:59.458 --> 00:11:02.517
I may have used up all the
goo on the test I already did.

141
00:11:02.541 --> 00:11:05.392
Like the one that told us it
wasn't a shaved chimpanzee.

142
00:11:05.416 --> 00:11:07.017
Or a coyote with mange.

143
00:11:07.041 --> 00:11:08.041
It's hopeless.

144
00:11:10.708 --> 00:11:11.726
Maybe not.

145
00:11:11.750 --> 00:11:15.517
You said the thing was doing
something inside Jack's mouth?

146
00:11:15.541 --> 00:11:17.142
Yeah. but I couldn't see what.

147
00:11:17.166 --> 00:11:19.059
- So we find out what.
- How?

148
00:11:19.083 --> 00:11:20.750
I do an autopsy on Jack.

149
00:11:21.625 --> 00:11:22.934
You're allowed to do that?

150
00:11:22.958 --> 00:11:26.392
Absolutely not. so we have to do it
fast. Before they cremate Jack's body.

151
00:11:26.416 --> 00:11:30.184
- We'll go to the funeral home tonight.
- Whoa! Have you lost your mind?

152
00:11:30.208 --> 00:11:31.559
It's not as crazy as it sounds.

153
00:11:31.583 --> 00:11:33.267
I know that place like
the back of my hand.

154
00:11:33.291 --> 00:11:35.351
They've got no security.
No video cameras.

155
00:11:35.375 --> 00:11:38.142
We'll be in and out before
anybody notices what we're doing.

156
00:11:38.166 --> 00:11:39.958
Or we could end up in jail.

157
00:11:42.666 --> 00:11:43.666
Look.

158
00:11:44.041 --> 00:11:45.041
You got two choices.

159
00:11:45.958 --> 00:11:46.958
We can give up.

160
00:11:48.083 --> 00:11:49.583
Or we can go all the way.

161
00:11:50.333 --> 00:11:52.601
We both know where the first one ends.

162
00:11:52.625 --> 00:11:54.916
Nobody knows where
the second one leads.

163
00:11:56.583 --> 00:11:57.833
What do you want to do?

164
00:12:00.208 --> 00:12:01.958
Whose golf cart are we gonna take?

165
00:12:14.125 --> 00:12:18.458
Ever since the kids moved
out and Judy moved on.

166
00:12:19.208 --> 00:12:23.767
I've been searching for
proof that there's more to life

167
00:12:23.791 --> 00:12:25.791
than just knockin' about…

168
00:12:27.916 --> 00:12:29.375
And hangin' out.

169
00:12:33.041 --> 00:12:36.125
I looked in books. in religion.

170
00:12:38.000 --> 00:12:43.250
Spent a good time with
psychedelics. and I didn't find shit.

171
00:12:48.083 --> 00:12:49.750
Till the day you died.

172
00:12:56.833 --> 00:13:00.583
For the first time. I saw
something I could not explain.

173
00:13:03.833 --> 00:13:05.125
Something more.

174
00:13:08.958 --> 00:13:11.875
I'm sorry you had to
pay the price. brooksy.

175
00:13:17.250 --> 00:13:18.875
The path is calling me.

176
00:13:24.375 --> 00:13:25.791
I'MMA get to the end.

177
00:13:26.791 --> 00:13:29.541
And I'm gonna look god right in the eye.

178
00:13:30.041 --> 00:13:31.666
Even if it burns me.

179
00:13:42.000 --> 00:13:44.416
Flights of angels. brooksy.

180
00:13:46.958 --> 00:13:48.375
Flights of angels.

181
00:14:25.208 --> 00:14:26.625
Just get in.

182
00:14:41.916 --> 00:14:44.250
Some wear leather. some wear lace

183
00:14:45.208 --> 00:14:47.916
some wear makeup on their face

184
00:14:48.625 --> 00:14:50.916
some are young. some are old

185
00:14:51.666 --> 00:14:54.458
some too hot. some too cold.

186
00:14:58.750 --> 00:15:00.226
Renee. hey. What's up?

187
00:15:00.250 --> 00:15:02.767
Paz. Sorry to call so late…

188
00:15:02.791 --> 00:15:07.142
I just got an alert from your camera.
so I'm gonna head over there…

189
00:15:07.166 --> 00:15:08.726
Whoa. whoa. whoa. Hold on.

190
00:15:08.750 --> 00:15:10.226
…and check it out.

191
00:15:10.250 --> 00:15:12.142
My shift is almost
done. I'll meet you there.

192
00:15:12.166 --> 00:15:14.267
Don't go in without me.

193
00:15:14.291 --> 00:15:15.625
No promises.

194
00:15:20.708 --> 00:15:23.851
…to the shear line. which
will allow the plug to rotate.

195
00:15:23.875 --> 00:15:25.916
Insert your pick into the keyhole.

196
00:15:26.500 --> 00:15:27.642
Starting at the back.

197
00:15:27.666 --> 00:15:29.601
apply gentle pressure
on the tension wrench

198
00:15:29.625 --> 00:15:30.892
as you lift each pin.

199
00:15:30.916 --> 00:15:33.666
- You're taking too long!
- I've never done this before!

200
00:15:35.208 --> 00:15:37.017
- You should identify…
- can I try?

201
00:15:37.041 --> 00:15:38.809
I've almost got it.

202
00:15:38.833 --> 00:15:39.833
You're never gonna…

203
00:15:48.291 --> 00:15:49.375
This way.

204
00:16:02.166 --> 00:16:03.476
Sam.

205
00:16:03.500 --> 00:16:05.166
Hey. What's wrong?

206
00:16:09.000 --> 00:16:10.166
Sam.

207
00:16:13.500 --> 00:16:14.958
What was that?

208
00:16:17.541 --> 00:16:18.541
Let's go.

209
00:16:40.208 --> 00:16:41.267
God!

210
00:16:41.291 --> 00:16:43.875
Stay back. Do not move.

211
00:16:47.291 --> 00:16:49.291
How old is that pepper spray. Judy?

212
00:16:50.958 --> 00:16:53.166
It's expired. 2002.

213
00:16:53.958 --> 00:16:56.351
- Shit!
- Have you been following us?

214
00:16:56.375 --> 00:16:57.708
I damn well have.

215
00:16:58.208 --> 00:17:00.059
I saw you. the both of you.

216
00:17:00.083 --> 00:17:03.309
with that hammer and
then all of the crazy lights.

217
00:17:03.333 --> 00:17:04.476
Take it easy. Judy.

218
00:17:04.500 --> 00:17:06.309
Don't tell me to take it easy.

219
00:17:06.333 --> 00:17:08.017
Jack is dead.

220
00:17:08.041 --> 00:17:10.392
He's dead. and I think
you two know something.

221
00:17:10.416 --> 00:17:11.351
We can explain.

222
00:17:11.375 --> 00:17:12.750
Well. then talk fast.

223
00:17:14.333 --> 00:17:15.726
It's complicated.

224
00:17:15.750 --> 00:17:19.142
Well. simplify it. or I
will pull this fire alarm.

225
00:17:19.166 --> 00:17:20.684
You don't want to do that!

226
00:17:20.708 --> 00:17:24.226
What I want is for you to
tell me the truth right now.

227
00:17:24.250 --> 00:17:25.476
Did you kill Jack?

228
00:17:25.500 --> 00:17:27.017
Of course not.

229
00:17:27.041 --> 00:17:28.476
Why should I believe you?

230
00:17:28.500 --> 00:17:30.750
How long have we been friends. Judy?

231
00:17:31.500 --> 00:17:33.125
- You know me.
- Get back.

232
00:17:33.916 --> 00:17:36.059
I may be many things. but I'm not a liar.

233
00:17:36.083 --> 00:17:37.684
You lied to me this morning.

234
00:17:37.708 --> 00:17:38.976
That doesn't count.

235
00:17:39.000 --> 00:17:40.625
Jack was murdered.

236
00:17:41.958 --> 00:17:44.291
Not by us.

237
00:17:45.083 --> 00:17:46.291
By who?

238
00:17:47.416 --> 00:17:49.351
The answer lies behind that door.

239
00:17:49.375 --> 00:17:52.916
Now. if you pull that alarm.
we'll never know the truth.

240
00:17:53.416 --> 00:17:55.000
I'm hoping you won't.

241
00:17:56.000 --> 00:17:58.416
because we all want the same thing.

242
00:17:59.666 --> 00:18:00.875
Justice

243
00:18:02.125 --> 00:18:03.250
for Jack.

244
00:18:13.416 --> 00:18:14.416
Okay.

245
00:18:15.416 --> 00:18:18.083
Okay. Show me.

246
00:19:12.958 --> 00:19:14.833
Who's there? Come out!

247
00:19:15.333 --> 00:19:17.101
Hey! Stop.

248
00:19:17.125 --> 00:19:18.458
Fuck!

249
00:19:20.333 --> 00:19:21.541
Are you okay?

250
00:19:22.083 --> 00:19:24.875
No. You scared the shit out of me!

251
00:19:46.625 --> 00:19:49.750
You two may want to clear out.

252
00:19:51.250 --> 00:19:52.250
I'll stay.

253
00:19:53.541 --> 00:19:54.541
Okay.

254
00:20:01.833 --> 00:20:02.833
Yep.

255
00:20:15.125 --> 00:20:16.291
Jack.

256
00:20:29.833 --> 00:20:32.541
You may want to… follow her lead.

257
00:20:33.500 --> 00:20:36.559
This next part… isn't very palatable.

258
00:20:36.583 --> 00:20:37.642
I can handle it.

259
00:20:37.666 --> 00:20:43.291
Well. there'll be packing in
every cavity. lots of it. and…

260
00:20:44.458 --> 00:20:45.750
When I…

261
00:20:47.291 --> 00:20:50.875
Unseal his mouth. he may
release fluids and odors.

262
00:20:52.041 --> 00:20:53.208
I'll go check on Judy.

263
00:20:54.208 --> 00:20:55.250
Good thinking.

264
00:21:09.333 --> 00:21:11.226
I thought we could use this.

265
00:21:11.250 --> 00:21:12.291
I know I could.

266
00:21:12.791 --> 00:21:14.601
Yeah. this doesn't make sense.

267
00:21:14.625 --> 00:21:17.517
The camera is designed to
activate when it senses motion.

268
00:21:17.541 --> 00:21:20.267
But it's like it can't see
whatever knocked the bin over.

269
00:21:20.291 --> 00:21:23.166
which… doesn't make sense.

270
00:21:23.833 --> 00:21:25.142
Drink this.

271
00:21:25.166 --> 00:21:26.291
It'll help.

272
00:21:28.083 --> 00:21:29.583
Thanks.

273
00:21:33.041 --> 00:21:36.226
Screw it. I'll swap the camera
tomorrow. It must be busted.

274
00:21:36.250 --> 00:21:39.476
I'll leave the feed on in case
our thief decides to come back.

275
00:21:39.500 --> 00:21:42.059
You know. it sounded
more like an animal.

276
00:21:42.083 --> 00:21:43.392
Like a raccoon?

277
00:21:43.416 --> 00:21:45.142
No. not at all.

278
00:21:45.166 --> 00:21:48.142
Maybe somebody's messing with
you. Do you have any enemies?

279
00:21:48.166 --> 00:21:49.916
No. I killed them all.

280
00:21:50.791 --> 00:21:51.875
I respect that.

281
00:21:57.375 --> 00:21:59.541
Although it could be my ex-husband.

282
00:22:00.125 --> 00:22:02.750
He's what the French
call a fucking asshole.

283
00:22:03.458 --> 00:22:04.517
Tell me more.

284
00:22:04.541 --> 00:22:07.000
No. that would take all night.

285
00:22:07.583 --> 00:22:08.958
I got all night.

286
00:22:10.250 --> 00:22:11.416
All right.

287
00:22:31.125 --> 00:22:33.291
How long have you
known about me and Jack?

288
00:22:35.583 --> 00:22:37.625
I saw that look you gave Wally.

289
00:22:44.833 --> 00:22:46.875
Since the night of the barbecue.

290
00:22:48.208 --> 00:22:49.500
What gave us away?

291
00:22:51.083 --> 00:22:52.458
Tiger balm.

292
00:22:53.791 --> 00:22:56.000
Hey. no judgment here.

293
00:22:56.541 --> 00:22:58.291
No judgments accepted.

294
00:23:03.583 --> 00:23:06.875
Art and I have been married 44 years.

295
00:23:07.833 --> 00:23:10.184
We met at Berkeley in the '70s.

296
00:23:10.208 --> 00:23:11.416
You dig?

297
00:23:12.166 --> 00:23:13.958
Everything's everything?

298
00:23:14.958 --> 00:23:15.958
Sure.

299
00:23:16.916 --> 00:23:20.125
I was a bouncy-tittied ground breaker.

300
00:23:21.250 --> 00:23:24.916
Art was a counterculture shit-stirrer.

301
00:23:25.541 --> 00:23:28.041
We both had big-ass hair.

302
00:23:29.208 --> 00:23:30.583
Big ideas.

303
00:23:31.166 --> 00:23:32.166
Right.

304
00:23:33.875 --> 00:23:35.976
We did shit how we did it.

305
00:23:36.000 --> 00:23:38.416
We decided to marry.

306
00:23:39.541 --> 00:23:41.666
We decided to have kids.

307
00:23:42.291 --> 00:23:43.416
And when…

308
00:23:45.583 --> 00:23:47.375
We decided together.

309
00:23:49.666 --> 00:23:51.267
We're family. Sam.

310
00:23:51.291 --> 00:23:53.166
Every step of the way.

311
00:23:54.208 --> 00:23:55.291
That's nice.

312
00:23:55.958 --> 00:23:58.041
And we fuck who we want to fuck.

313
00:23:59.208 --> 00:24:00.750
Only rule was

314
00:24:01.666 --> 00:24:03.333
don't fall in love.

315
00:24:08.041 --> 00:24:09.916
But you fell in love with Jack?

316
00:24:14.000 --> 00:24:15.083
I did.

317
00:24:17.458 --> 00:24:19.101
I'm not deluded.

318
00:24:19.125 --> 00:24:23.375
I see the… the years
etched across my face.

319
00:24:23.875 --> 00:24:26.250
And I feel the weight of my body.

320
00:24:27.708 --> 00:24:28.791
But Jack…

321
00:24:31.250 --> 00:24:33.708
Jack saw the girl in me.

322
00:24:34.708 --> 00:24:36.166
He could see it.

323
00:24:37.666 --> 00:24:39.875
And he respected the woman.

324
00:24:42.416 --> 00:24:46.333
Jack could… he could… Jack saw us.

325
00:24:47.750 --> 00:24:49.250
The way we wish we were.

326
00:24:51.208 --> 00:24:52.541
He was good.

327
00:24:55.125 --> 00:24:56.666
And now he's gone.

328
00:24:59.708 --> 00:25:01.958
Everybody loved Jack.

329
00:25:04.333 --> 00:25:07.500
And Jack certainly did love everybody.

330
00:25:08.958 --> 00:25:12.458
I was just… one in the line.

331
00:25:15.875 --> 00:25:17.916
That's not the way Jack described you.

332
00:25:20.500 --> 00:25:22.017
What did he say?

333
00:25:22.041 --> 00:25:24.291
He was seeing someone special.

334
00:25:38.208 --> 00:25:39.750
They say that.

335
00:25:40.458 --> 00:25:42.500
grief is

336
00:25:43.000 --> 00:25:45.708
less like a line and more like…

337
00:25:48.333 --> 00:25:49.625
like a pyramid.

338
00:25:50.666 --> 00:25:51.833
With…

339
00:25:54.416 --> 00:25:57.500
Acceptance… at the bottom.

340
00:25:59.041 --> 00:26:00.184
Who said that?

341
00:26:00.208 --> 00:26:01.767
My son-in-law.

342
00:26:01.791 --> 00:26:02.875
Is he simple?

343
00:26:05.625 --> 00:26:07.500
No. no.

344
00:26:08.916 --> 00:26:10.500
He's a college professor.

345
00:26:11.041 --> 00:26:12.476
A pyramid.

346
00:26:12.500 --> 00:26:14.083
Bless his heart.

347
00:26:26.000 --> 00:26:28.083
There's something you need to see.

348
00:26:30.166 --> 00:26:33.750
Okay. I didn't find anything
unusual on Jack's body.

349
00:26:34.541 --> 00:26:38.708
except for these marks
in the back of his throat.

350
00:26:39.208 --> 00:26:40.267
See for yourself.

351
00:26:40.291 --> 00:26:41.500
What are those?

352
00:26:42.500 --> 00:26:43.500
Puncture wounds.

353
00:26:44.458 --> 00:26:47.833
Mostly scarred over.
although some fresh.

354
00:26:49.041 --> 00:26:51.291
All leading right to the
base of Jack's brain.

355
00:26:54.000 --> 00:26:56.434
This could be what that
thing was doing to Jack.

356
00:26:56.458 --> 00:26:57.434
What thing?

357
00:26:57.458 --> 00:26:59.559
It was… it was convulsing.

358
00:26:59.583 --> 00:27:02.059
Like it was… like it was feeding on him.

359
00:27:02.083 --> 00:27:06.583
Hey. it's about goddamn time you
guys tell me exactly what is going on.

360
00:27:10.208 --> 00:27:11.601
So. the business took off.

361
00:27:11.625 --> 00:27:14.184
I handled the artists.
He handled the books.

362
00:27:14.208 --> 00:27:15.392
But when I left him…

363
00:27:15.416 --> 00:27:17.684
- He knew where the money was.
- Right.

364
00:27:17.708 --> 00:27:20.976
I mean. what he didn't
outright steal. he sued me for.

365
00:27:21.000 --> 00:27:22.809
And the legal fees and all that.

366
00:27:22.833 --> 00:27:27.142
so I ended up having to
move in here with my mother.

367
00:27:27.166 --> 00:27:28.351
Humbling.

368
00:27:28.375 --> 00:27:30.601
It was a nightmare.

369
00:27:30.625 --> 00:27:34.583
But. you know. she died. and
then I just kept on living here.

370
00:27:35.875 --> 00:27:37.041
What about you?

371
00:27:37.958 --> 00:27:39.392
I grew up local.

372
00:27:39.416 --> 00:27:41.726
joined with the first
band headed out of town

373
00:27:41.750 --> 00:27:43.101
and never looked back.

374
00:27:43.125 --> 00:27:44.976
Yet here you are.

375
00:27:45.000 --> 00:27:47.434
Yeah. well. my big sister
got in a car accident.

376
00:27:48.375 --> 00:27:50.625
I came back to help with my nephews.

377
00:27:51.250 --> 00:27:54.166
This was the only place willing
to hire a drummer with no résumé.

378
00:27:54.958 --> 00:27:56.226
How's your sister now?

379
00:27:56.250 --> 00:27:59.101
They fused her spine with steel rods.

380
00:27:59.125 --> 00:28:00.767
Yeah. she's indestructible.

381
00:28:00.791 --> 00:28:03.375
It's a terrifying prospect to a little brother.

382
00:28:04.916 --> 00:28:06.916
Is that… is that glastonbury?

383
00:28:08.291 --> 00:28:09.291
This?

384
00:28:09.833 --> 00:28:10.833
Yeah.

385
00:28:11.291 --> 00:28:12.351
It is.

386
00:28:12.375 --> 00:28:14.833
2010. I think.

387
00:28:15.375 --> 00:28:17.559
- I was there.
- No. you weren't.

388
00:28:17.583 --> 00:28:20.851
- No. hand to god. I'm right…
- no. you were not.

389
00:28:20.875 --> 00:28:22.809
Over here… somewhere.

390
00:28:22.833 --> 00:28:25.392
So you really splurged on the tickets?

391
00:28:25.416 --> 00:28:28.458
Yeah. well. some of us
don't have suit money.

392
00:28:38.083 --> 00:28:40.916
Would it be okay if I kissed you?

393
00:28:42.166 --> 00:28:43.250
Yes.

394
00:29:19.041 --> 00:29:20.083
Take this off.

395
00:29:21.625 --> 00:29:22.916
You didn't ask.

396
00:29:23.583 --> 00:29:24.666
Right.

397
00:29:36.125 --> 00:29:37.125
Come here.

398
00:30:18.958 --> 00:30:21.125
What are you up to. scar?

399
00:30:24.541 --> 00:30:25.726
Go for Hank.

400
00:30:25.750 --> 00:30:27.517
Hank. a lady walking her dog said

401
